.TH EYECALIB 1 "2026" "tobii4c" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
eyecalib \- fullscreen gaze calibration utility for Tobii Eye Tracker 4C

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eyecalib

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B eyecalib
provides fullscreen calibration for the Tobii Eye Tracker 4C
under Linux/X11.

The utility collects gaze samples for a 3x3 calibration mesh
used by:

.B eyemouse

Calibration improves:

- fullscreen reachability
- edge precision
- cursor stability
- corner access
- asymmetric distortion correction

.SH CALIBRATION PROCESS
The calibration process:

.nf
fullscreen targets
    -> gaze sample collection
    -> sample filtering
    -> calibration mesh generation
    -> persistent calibration storage
.fi

.SH CALIBRATION TARGETS
The calibration uses a 3x3 fullscreen target layout:

.nf
P00  P01  P02
P10  P11  P12
P20  P21  P22
.fi

Targets are intentionally placed near display borders
to improve fullscreen reachability.

.SH CALIBRATION STORAGE
Calibration data is written to:

.nf
~/.local/tobii_4c/calx11.conf
.fi

Example:

.nf
0.052524 0.075656 0.050000 0.050000
.fi

Format:

.nf
raw_x raw_y target_x target_y
.fi

.SH CALIBRATION MATHEMATICS
Each calibration sample stores:

- measured Tobii gaze position
- expected screen position

Example:

.nf
0.523789 0.455566 -> 0.500000 0.500000
.fi

Meaning:

- tracker measured 52.4% horizontal gaze
- actual target was 50%

The runtime later derives local barycentric mesh warp correction.

.SH BARYCENTRIC MESH MAPPING
The stabtion derived from calibration samples.

Conceptually:

.nf
triangle barycentric coordinates\n   achability
- fullscreen coverage
- corner precision

.SH RUNTIME FILTERING
Calibration performs:

- invalid sample rejection
- realtime smoothing
- sample stabilization
- gaze averaging

This reduces:

- jitter
- unstable fixation
- noisy gaze samples

.SH X11 REQUIREMENT
The calibration utility currently requires:

- X11
- fullscreen override-redirect windows
- X11 pointer control

Wayland is unsupported.

Check:

.nf
$ echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
x11
.fi

.SH FILES
.nf
~/.local/tobii_4c/calx11.conf
.fi

.SH CURRENT STABLE RUNTIME
The current stable runtime actively uses:

- barylation
- 3x3 calibration mesh
- X11 cursor mapping
- realtime smoothing

The following features are experimental or incomplete:

- bootstrap geometry import
- C12 runtime
- projective warp
- head compensated reprojection
- full 3D geometry correction

.SH EXAMPLE
Run calibration:

.nf
$ eyecalib
.fi

Run eyemouse afterwards:

.nf
$ eyemouse
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR eyemouse (1)

